Three children suffered serious burn wounds after a house in which they were sleeping in Hlanganani, Limpopo, caught fire, police said on Wednesday. The incident happened after 1am on Wednesday after their mother left them sleeping and went to a nearby shebeen, said spokesman Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe. While she was busy there she noticed that her house was on fire. She immediately rushed back home and called for assistance from neighbours, he said. The children, aged 4, 5 and 7, were rescued and taken to hospital. He reiterated the South African Police Services call to all community members, especially mothers, to apply child safety measures and look after their children at all times. African News Agency (ANA)